nts1.n: CARLOS RENÉ: CUMBIA EN MARACAY - VENEZUELAN CUMBIA & PORRO (R)
nts1.d: Spanning the late 1950s to the late 1970s, this selection highlights Venezuela’s take on big band cumbia. With strong ties to Colombian cumbia, especially in cities like Maracaibo and Caracas, local orchestras blended its rhythms with their own style. Some tracks reinterpret Colombian classics with a distinct Venezuelan touch, while many are original compositions that showcase the country’s unique approach to the genre.

nts1.n: SOUNDS ON SCREEN: BRIAN DE PALMA (R)
nts1.d:
Scores, needle drops and iconic moments from the filmography of Brian De Palma - once a star of the New Hollywood movement of the 60s and 70s, De Palma famously admitted he wished to become the "American Godard". His style is broad, and allusive to his cinematic heroes – Godard, Hitchcock, Antonioni – creating cult classic and popcorn blockbusters alike, with the patchy critical reception that only a fiercely independent creative spirit could earn. 
Selected and mixed by Florence Scott-Anderton.

nts2.d:
Radical Empathy - In times of war, listening is rebellion. Somewhere
between ambient, new age, neo soul, vintage erotic soundtracks and
resistance voices, peace sounds human, sensual, and defiant. Voices once
silenced invite us to feel, to love, to build a renewed, inclusive world
where tenderness becomes protest.
Katy Cardie invites you on a journey to Andalusia, where the voices of the gypsies still echo, expressing both the pain of being kept apart and the joy of being together.
Songs that sound like dew even before it rains. My playlist for solace & bedtime :)
A melodramatic clatter of popular music from everywhere infused with hope and love.
This Japanese ambient mix was inspired by the serene peace and tranquility of a train journey through the Japanese countryside, inviting contemplation of the endless beautiful landscapes.

nts2.n: The Peace Industrial Complex W/ Sandra Rachdi
nts2.d:
A broadcast from the barricades and beneath the black flags. A peace punk, anarcho-punk , and UK82 mix tracing the uneasy tension between noise and hope. Songs of anti-war, anti-state, and anti-system fury collide with fragile dreams of peace, love, and mutual aid.
Peace as feedback // Rebellion as rhythm.

We're butterflying through a dark sky. "Peace" is what we are hungering for. Love is our weapon. 
How words and music can heal a heart and let us be carried by the wind, through the sound of a flute, an electric guitar riff, or powerful soul voices. 
This mix is composed of sounds that have been bringing peace or grounding, at different times of my life, somehow bringing a feeling of an in-between the earth and the sky, going from heaviness to heaven, alchemizing grief into jasmines, growing butterfly wings. The selection present different genres but I tried to build a journey that could bring joy, calmness, and high vibrations (selection was hard!) In this sea of words pronounced by the different artists, or told by the various instruments that are playing, I added some words from Maya Angelou and from my heart.

nts2.n: what does peace sound like w/ ulittlekitty
nts2.d: to me, peace should sound like that special place you go to, your shelter, whenever you have to take a break from the world. peace sounds like a river and the trees that reflect in its water. peace sounds like peace of mind. i chose all the sounds based on if they made me think of my special place. i hope they can bring some peace to you as well <3

While we may have all tried to portray this abstract feeling coming from afar without ever getting closer, I puzzled up a set of pieces each providing this inner feeling of peace - a quietude of mind allowing a more serene vision of this tumultuous world in which we live.

Music that brings me a sense of peace. While the focus is very much on sounds with a celestial feel, I wanted to include some more textural pieces to hopefully add some emotional depth. I hope you enjoy the mix and that you find some respite within.
A love letter to the moon, a place where any type of light and darkness are both possible and beautiful.
there is a dove living inside of my chest and it sees us as family.

For me, peace is synonymous with home — a corner of the world that we carve out and enrich with every facet of our identity. Here I offer up a set of tracks to play when you want to feel the walls pulsing with sweet, sweet soul.

nts2.n: Where Earth Meets Sky w/ Chi-Chi Usagi
nts2.d: I’m coming out from two of the toughest years of my life, and the music you are about to hear is what saved me. This mix features the song I walked down the aisle to at my wedding a few months before my life was flipped upside down, songs that held me through lonely nights dealing with withdrawals from an addiction I’d held onto for 10 years, songs that comforted me when I was kicked out of my career, songs that I danced on the roof to in the rain during the last nights in my home, Brooklyn, NY. All of this music has held me through moments that tested my willpower. The love that I have for myself and the love that I have for God is what got me through it all. May this little snippet of my peace touch something within you.
